@baseUrl = http://localhost:5285

### ==================== Authors ====================

### List all authors
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/authors?page=1&pageSize=10

### Search authors by name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/authors?search=Orwell&page=1&pageSize=10

### Get author by ID (Jane Austen)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/authors/1

### Get author by ID (George Orwell — has multiple books)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/authors/2

### Create a new author
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/authors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Margaret",
  "lastName": "Atwood",
  "biography": "Canadian poet, novelist, literary critic, essayist, and environmental activist.",
  "birthDate": "1939-11-18",
  "country": "Canada"
}

### Update an author
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/authors/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Austen",
  "biography": "English novelist known primarily for her six major novels, which interpret, critique, and comment upon the British landed gentry at the end of the 18th century.",
  "birthDate": "1775-12-16",
  "country": "United Kingdom"
}

### Delete an author (will fail if author has books)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/authors/1

### ==================== Categories ====================

### List all categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/categories?page=1&pageSize=20

### Get category by ID (Fiction)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/1

### Get category by ID (Science Fiction)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/2

### Create a new category
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Philosophy",
  "description": "Books about philosophical thought and theory"
}

### Update a category
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/3
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "History",
  "description": "Non-fiction works about historical events, periods, and figures"
}

### Delete a category (will fail if category has books)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/categories/1

### ==================== Books ====================

### List all books
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?page=1&pageSize=10

### Search books by title
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?search=1984&page=1&pageSize=10

### Search books by author name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?search=Murakami&page=1&pageSize=10

### Filter books by availability (available only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?available=true&page=1&pageSize=10

### Filter books not available
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?available=false&page=1&pageSize=10

### Sort books by title descending
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?sortBy=title&sortOrder=desc&page=1&pageSize=10

### Sort books by year
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books?sortBy=year&page=1&pageSize=10

### Get book by ID (Pride and Prejudice)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/1

### Get book by ID (1984 — has active loan and reservation)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/2

### Get book by ID (Norwegian Wood — no available copies)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/5

### Create a new book
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Handmaid's Tale",
  "isbn": "978-0-38-549081-8",
  "publisher": "Anchor Books",
  "publicationYear": 1985,
  "description": "A dystopian novel set in a totalitarian state.",
  "pageCount": 311,
  "language": "English",
  "totalCopies": 3,
  "authorIds": [1],
  "categoryIds": [1, 2]
}

### Update a book
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/books/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Pride and Prejudice",
  "isbn": "978-0-14-028329-7",
  "publisher": "Penguin Classics",
  "publicationYear": 1813,
  "description": "A romantic novel of manners, widely considered one of the greatest novels in the English language.",
  "pageCount": 432,
  "language": "English",
  "totalCopies": 4,
  "authorIds": [1],
  "categoryIds": [1, 6]
}

### Delete a book (will fail if it has active loans)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/books/2

### Get book loan history
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/2/loans

### Get book reservations queue
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books/5/reservations

### ==================== Patrons ====================

### List all patrons
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons?page=1&pageSize=10

### Search patrons by name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons?search=Alice&page=1&pageSize=10

### Search patrons by email
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons?search=bob.smith&page=1&pageSize=10

### Filter patrons by membership type
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons?membershipType=Premium&page=1&pageSize=10

### Filter Student patrons
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons?membershipType=Student&page=1&pageSize=10

### Get patron by ID (Alice — Premium, active)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/1

### Get patron by ID (Bob — has overdue loan and unpaid fine)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/2

### Get patron by ID (Frank — inactive)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/6

### Create a new patron
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Grace",
  "lastName": "Lee",
  "email": "grace.lee@email.com",
  "phone": "555-0107",
  "address": "111 Maple St",
  "membershipType": "Standard"
}

### Update a patron
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Alice",
  "lastName": "Johnson",
  "email": "alice.johnson@email.com",
  "phone": "555-0101",
  "address": "123 Main St, Apt 4B",
  "membershipType": "Premium"
}

### Deactivate a patron (will fail if patron has active loans)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/1

### Get patron's loans (all)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/1/loans

### Get patron's active loans
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/2/loans?status=active

### Get patron's overdue loans
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/2/loans?status=overdue

### Get patron's reservations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/1/reservations

### Get patron's fines (all)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/2/fines

### Get patron's unpaid fines
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patrons/2/fines?status=unpaid

### ==================== Loans ====================

### List all loans
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans?page=1&pageSize=20

### List active loans only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans?status=Active&page=1&pageSize=20

### List returned loans
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans?status=Returned&page=1&pageSize=20

### List overdue loans using filter
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans?overdue=true&page=1&pageSize=20

### Get loan by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/1

### Get overdue loans (also flags newly overdue)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/overdue

### Check out a book — normal checkout (Book 4 for Patron 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 4,
  "patronId": 1
}

### Check out a book — test: inactive patron (Frank, id=6)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 4,
  "patronId": 6
}

### Check out a book — test: no available copies (Norwegian Wood, id=5)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 5,
  "patronId": 1
}

### Return a book (Loan 1 — active loan)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/1/return

### Return a book (Loan 4 — overdue, will generate fine)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/4/return

### Renew a loan (Loan 2 — active)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/2/renew

### Renew a loan — test: overdue loan should fail (Loan 4)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/4/renew

### Renew a loan — test: pending reservations should fail (Loan 3 — book 5 has reservations)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/loans/3/renew

### ==================== Reservations ====================

### List all reservations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations?page=1&pageSize=20

### List pending reservations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations?status=Pending&page=1&pageSize=20

### List ready reservations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations?status=Ready&page=1&pageSize=20

### Get reservation by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/1

### Get ready reservation
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/3

### Create a reservation — normal (Book 2 for Patron 4)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 2,
  "patronId": 4
}

### Create a reservation — test: patron already has active loan on this book (Book 5, Patron 3)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 5,
  "patronId": 3
}

### Cancel a reservation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/1/cancel

### Fulfill a ready reservation (Reservation 3 is Ready for Book 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/3/fulfill

### ==================== Fines ====================

### List all fines
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/fines?page=1&pageSize=20

### List unpaid fines
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/fines?status=Unpaid&page=1&pageSize=20

### List paid fines
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/fines?status=Paid&page=1&pageSize=20

### Get fine by ID (unpaid)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/fines/1

### Get fine by ID (paid)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/fines/3

### Pay a fine
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/fines/1/pay

### Waive a fine
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/fines/2/waive
